#{200}{}{Louie, he was from Reno himself. He wanted to bring back the "Golden Age" when everyone had enough, but he realized he couldn't do it. Reno's just not the same place it was back then. Big Louie couldn't take it and fucked off to the wasteland, leaving Thompson and me in charge. Thompson was supposed to hold the mayor's office and I was in charge of the local defense. We were supposed to be partners, but it didn't work out.}
{200}{}{路易，他是雷诺人。他想在大家都吃饱了的时候把“黄金时代”带回来，但他意识到自己做不到。里诺和那时候不一样了。大路易受不了了，就滚到荒地去了，让汤普森和我负责。汤普森本该担任市长的职务，而我负责当地的防务。我们本来是搭档的，但没成功。 -- Louie, he was from Reno himself. He wanted to bring back the "Golden Age" when everyone had enough, but he realized he couldn't do it. Reno's just not the same place it was back then. Big Louie couldn't take it and fucked off to the wasteland, leaving Thompson and me in charge. Thompson was supposed to hold the mayor's office and I was in charge of the local defense. We were supposed to be partners, but it didn't work out.}
#{201}{}{Why?}
{201}{}{为什么？ -- Why?}
#{202}{}{Because running a city ain't like the gang shit we were doing before, you get it? You can't keep this many people in line with just violence. You need to *lead* them. You need an *idea* that makes them *want* you in charge. And Thompson and I have different ideas. Thompson just wants to enslave everyone, like just after the Great War, when the mayor forced people to work and crushed any resistance. But those were different times. It won't work now.}
{202}{}{因为管理一个城市不像我们以前做的那样，明白吗？你不能让这么多人和暴力保持一致。你需要领导他们。你需要一个让他们想让你负责的想法。汤普森和我有不同的想法。汤普森只是想奴役所有人，就像二战后，市长强迫人们工作，镇压任何抵抗。但那是不同的时代。现在不行了。 -- Because running a city ain't like the gang shit we were doing before, you get it? You can't keep this many people in line with just violence. You need to *lead* them. You need an *idea* that makes them *want* you in charge. And Thompson and I have different ideas. Thompson just wants to enslave everyone, like just after the Great War, when the mayor forced people to work and crushed any resistance. But those were different times. It won't work now.}
#{203}{}{So what's your idea?}
{203}{}{你有什么想法？ -- So what's your idea?}
#{204}{}{Once Thompson's out of the way, I'll lead a militia strong enough to keep order. Then I'll organize the business leaders into a guild that make decisions for the town as a group. The militia will protect the guild and get a percentage of their profits in return. [he snaps his fingers] Simple as that.}
{204}{}{一旦汤普森出事，我将率领一支足够强大的民兵维持秩序。然后我会把商业领袖组织成一个公会，作为一个团体为小镇做决定。民兵会保护公会，并从中获得一定比例的利润作为回报。就这么简单。 -- Once Thompson's out of the way, I'll lead a militia strong enough to keep order. Then I'll organize the business leaders into a guild that make decisions for the town as a group. The militia will protect the guild and get a percentage of their profits in return. [he snaps his fingers] Simple as that.}
#{205}{}{Do you really think the business leaders will be willing to share power?}
{205}{}{你真的认为商界领袖会愿意分享权力吗？ -- Do you really think the business leaders will be willing to share power?}
#{206}{}{Yeah, yeah, they'll bitch and moan, but the truth is they've been fighting forever and it's only caused them trouble. How long can this go on? They'll come around, especially when they figure out what'll happen if they're the only ones *without* the militia's help.}
{206}{}{是的，是的，他们会抱怨和呻吟，但事实是他们一直在战斗，这只会给他们带来麻烦。这能持续多久？他们会回来的，尤其是当他们知道如果他们是唯一没有民兵帮助的人会发生什么的时候。 -- Yeah, yeah, they'll bitch and moan, but the truth is they've been fighting forever and it's only caused them trouble. How long can this go on? They'll come around, especially when they figure out what'll happen if they're the only ones *without* the militia's help.}
#{207}{}{Don't you want to be something greater than just the head of the militia?}
{207}{}{难道你不想成为比民兵首领更伟大的人物吗？ -- Don't you want to be something greater than just the head of the militia?}
#{208}{}{What else can I do, now that I'm neck-deep in this city's shit?! I told you, the old gang tactics won't work here. This isn't the wasteland, it's a city. The people here are smart and organized. But there's a good side to that - this city could do great things once I straighten it out. Once that happens... Being head of the militia will be enough for any man.}
{208}{}{我还可以做什么，现在我在这个城市的狗屎脖子深？！我告诉过你，旧的帮派战术在这里行不通。这不是荒地，这是一座城市。这里的人既聪明又有条理。但这也有好的一面――一旦我把它理顺，这个城市可以做大事。一旦发生了。。。当民兵队长对任何人都足够了。 -- What else can I do, now that I'm neck-deep in this city's shit?! I told you, the old gang tactics won't work here. This isn't the wasteland, it's a city. The people here are smart and organized. But there's a good side to that - this city could do great things once I straighten it out. Once that happens... Being head of the militia will be enough for any man.}
#{209}{}{Now I get it. Well, gotta go mind my own business. Thanks for explaining.}
{209}{}{现在我明白了。好吧，管好我自己的事。谢谢你的解释。 -- Now I get it. Well, gotta go mind my own business. Thanks for explaining.}
#{210}{}{Betty Paige is dead.}
{210}{}{贝蒂・佩吉死了。 -- Betty Paige is dead.}
#{211}{}{[He gives you a cunning look, then pulls out 100 dollars] That's all. Not enough? Then I'm sure you can find another job, since you've been working so many angles in this town. At this point, I need people who are fighting for more than just money. Take your payment and go - I don't need you anymore.}
{211}{}{[他狡猾地看了你一眼，然后掏出100美元]仅此而已。还不够？那么我相信你能找到另一份工作，因为你在这个镇上工作了这么多角度。在这一点上，我需要的不仅仅是为了钱而战斗的人。拿着你的钱走吧-我不再需要你了。 -- [He gives you a cunning look, then pulls out 100 dollars] That's all. Not enough? Then I'm sure you can find another job, since you've been working so many angles in this town. At this point, I need people who are fighting for more than just money. Take your payment and go - I don't need you anymore.}
